The paper is about Systematic Mapping Studies (SMSs) in Software Engineering (SE), which is a subfield of Computer Science. Therefore, cs.SE is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the quality of SMSs, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it relates to the evaluation of research. The paper also mentions the lack of SMSs in certain areas, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it relates to identifying gaps in research. The paper also mentions software design and construction as the most active areas in SE, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it relates to the development of software. Finally, the paper discusses the use of SE tools, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it relates to the use of technology in society.
